Hazel Cills | March 15, 2022 The first shot of Bonobo's Tiny Desk (home) concert is a little disorienting. What looks like the official Tiny Desk at NPR's Washington, D.C. headquarters is actually an eerily accurate miniature replication. Fit with scaled-down vinyl LPs and Bob Boilen's knickknacks, it was created by Cheronda Scott of CSpykerMiniatures and Kat Williams of Real Life Miniatures. item.description:
![CDATA[Da Captain Trips - Maths of the Elements (Full Album) Da Captain Trips is an instrumental psychedelic stoner rock band based in the north of Italy. Maths of the Elements is the fourth full length of the band and comes five years after ‚ÄúAdventures in the Upside Down‚Äù. This album is dedicated to Nature, its Elements, and the slow growth of everything. Each track wants to drive the listener to immerse themselves in a slow journey of awareness of the elements of nature. The songs breathe and develop slowly, are more dilated and improvised than ‚ÄúAdventures in the upside-down‚Äù.
Each Captain album is different from the previous one also thanks to the line-up changes that this time sees Bachis give way to Paolo ‚ÄúApollo‚Äù Negri on keyboards.
